     <body>
     <div type="dedication">
   <pb facs="13"/>
   <head>To his Friend, <hi>H. M.</hi>
   </head>
   <lg>
      <l>HOnour is due to him that doth advance,</l>
      <l>VNdoubted truth, with lively circumstance.</l>
      <l>MVch of this skill this Authour hath found out;</l>
      <l>PVts Sinto silence: questions out of doubt.</l>
      <l>HAving pursu'd the cause of desolation,</l>
      <l>RAising the hearts sweetly with meditation.</l>
      <l>YOur soules may see, their enemies descri'd,</l>
      <l>MAns wit is pliable, truly sanctified,</l>
      <l>IN laying siege, 'gainst sinne, thy Poetry,</l>
      <l>LEaves it accurst, in hellish destiny.</l>
      <l>LEt not thy conquest die, let's know the thing,</l>
      <l>SAlly forth little booke, feare no deadly sting.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
